  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6583.13 sitting just below the GEX flip at 6588, dealers are currently long gamma and will likely sell any push higher into the massive 6590-6600 gamma wall cluster (78K+ combined). The wall_break and gex_surge events indicate dealers just absorbed significant flow and are now positioned to provide heavy resistance above, while the PIN regime suggests they'll defend the downside near 6580 support. Key levels to watch: 6588 flip strike as the pivot, 6600 max gamma for selling pressure, and 6580 as the lower bound of this consolidation zone.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect SPX to get pinned between 6580-6600 with dealers capping both sides.",
